# Cynalytica AnalytICS Engine Add-On For Splunk

The Cynalytica AnalytICS Engine Add-On for Splunk enables you to seamlessly integrate Cynalytica's AnalytICS Engine data with your Splunk Instance.

The Add-On provides:
 - Seamless ingestion of AnalytICS Engine **metrics**, **audit events**, and **alerts**.
 - Splunk CIM compatibility of AnalytICS Engine **alerts**.

## Installation & Configuration

After downloading the Add-On from Splunkbase and uploading the Add-On to your Splunk instance, you will need to perform the following:

 1. Setup an Index for the Cynalytica AnalytICS Engine Add-On.
 2. Setup an HEC (HTTP Event Collector) in Splunk.

To send data over to Splunk, you will need to set up a Splunk Integration in the AnalytICS Engine, this can be done by:

 1. Navigate to Settings > Integrations > Splunk.
 2. Give the Integration a name and description.
 3. Fill in the Address with where your Splunk Instance is hosted or forwarder. Be sure to include the port. (Example: http://10.0.2.246:8088)
 4. Select desired subscriptions (metrics, alerts, audit events).
 5. Copy the token in your Splunk Instance's HEC into the Token field in the AnalytICS Engine.
 6. Assign an index if desired in the AnalytICS Engine or assign the index in the HEC in Splunk.
 7. Enable indexer acknowledgment if desired to prevent data loss.
